sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
At their wedding, Drogo gives Daenerys the silver as a gift. Daenerys declares that she is beautiful and asks Ser [[Jorah Mormont]] what the word for &quot;thank you&quot; is in [[Dothraki (language)|Dothraki]]. Jorah replies that there is no such word. Dany rides the silver as she and Drogo depart to consummate their marriage&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Winter is Coming]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

In pain due to her inexperience in horseback riding, Daenerys needs to be helped down from the silver by her handmaidens.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

Daenerys rides the silver through the [[Dothraki Sea]]&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Lord Snow]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; and on to [[Vaes Dothrak]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

After a [[wineseller]] is caught attempting to poison Daenerys, he is punished by being stripped and bound with a rope to the silver's saddle and is pulled along the road as the ''[[khalasar]]'' makes it's way to [[Lhazar]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[You Win or You Die]]&quot;.&lt;/ref&gt;

Daenerys leaps from the silver to help Drogo when he falls from his horse, a wound he received in his duel with [[Mago]] having festered due to treachery of [[Mirri Maz Duur]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Baelor]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 2]]===
The silver dies of starvation in the [[Red Waste]]. Daenerys takes her death very hard, as she was the first gift Drogo gave her.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The North Remembers]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
